The paper deals with graph drawing algorithms and their applications in routing schemes, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the study of planar graphs and their properties, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of greedy algorithms in the drawing of graphs also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.SI).
